Final Conclusion

This threat hunt identified suspicious local data staging activity on `vme-windows-hun`.

The investigation found that zip archive activity occurred on the device and that related process activity showed PowerShell execution, silent 7zip installation, and use of 7zip to compress employee data.

The activity was suspicious because it matched behavior commonly associated with insider threat preparation, including archive creation and local staging of data.

However, the reviewed network telemetry did not show clear evidence that the archived data was exfiltrated from the device.

The system was isolated, and the findings were reported to management for further action.

This project demonstrates the importance of monitoring archive creation, PowerShell execution, unauthorized tool installation, and network activity together when investigating possible insider threat behavior.
